@*
    Example 4 — Driving the control from your own UI.

    ActivateAsync(), CopyAsync() and ShareNativelyAsync() are public, so
    a @ref lets your own buttons drive the control. Useful when the share
    affordance belongs somewhere the component cannot sit — a toolbar, a
    keyboard shortcut, an end-of-article call to action.

    ActivateAsync() runs the full strategy: native sheet where allowed
    and available, list otherwise. ShareNativelyAsync() attempts only the
    sheet and returns a NativeShareOutcome so you can decide what a
    dismissal or an unsupported browser should mean in your flow.

    Two things worth keeping straight:

    - The ShareButton itself is still rendered, and still needs to be. It
      owns the list, the status region, and the focus contract. Hiding it
      with display:none would take the list away too; if you do not want
      the trigger visible, style .share-button-trigger — but then the
      control's accessible name has to live on YOUR button instead.

    - Your external button needs its own accessible name. Label names the
      component's trigger, not yours.
*@

@page "/examples/share-button/external-activation"
@rendermode InteractiveServer
@using LilyDesignSystem.Blazor.Helpers

<ShareButton @ref="_share"
             Label="Share this page"
             Targets="@Targets"
             CopyLabel="Copy link"
             CopiedLabel="Link copied"
             CopyFailedLabel="Could not copy — copy it from the address bar"
             OnCopy="@(url => Log($"copied {url}"))" />

<p>
    <button type="button" @onclick="ActivateAsync">Share this article</button>
    <button type="button" @onclick="CopyAsync">Copy the link</button>
</p>

<p aria-live="polite">@_last</p>

@code {
    private ShareButton? _share;
    private string _last = "";

    private async Task ActivateAsync()
    {
        if (_share is not null) await _share.ActivateAsync();
    }

    private async Task CopyAsync()
    {
        if (_share is not null) await _share.CopyAsync();
    }

    private void Log(string message)
    {
        _last = message;
        StateHasChanged();
    }

    private static readonly ShareTarget[] Targets =
    {
        new()
        {
            Id = "linkedin",
            Label = "LinkedIn",
            Href = (url, _, _) =>
                $"https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite/?url={Uri.EscapeDataString(url)}",
        },
    };
}
